file=AI & Agents/edge/operational/commands/edge-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "adopt this tech", "is it ready", "should we build on", "score this technology" \| tech-adoption-criteria \| /gate \| · tb=\| "watch list", "re-check", "what are we watching", "material event on X" \| watchlist-discipline \| /watch \| · tb=\| "pilot spec", "hand to proto", "pilot came back", "parked pilots" \| pilot-spec-handoff \| /pilot \| · tb=\| "landscape", "what's the state of <domain>", "update the landscape", "stale landscape" \| landscape-assets \| /landscape \| · p:Precedence=1. AI-model/method-shaped candidates route to forge at first sight — the shape test precedes any scoring here.\n2. Re-checks refresh stale landscapes FIRST (scoring on stale data is laundering).\n3. A returned pilot verdict outranks new scoring requests (close loops before opening them).\n